Instead of hardcoding the list of themes (`["classic", "chicago"]`) in the test parametrization, we can use `available_themes()`. This ensures that any newly added themes in the future are automatically covered by this SVG rendering test without requiring manual updates to the test suite.

```suggestion
@pytest.mark.parametrize("theme", available_themes())
def test_every_design_builds_valid_svg(theme):
```

